      "body" : "Tested the patched version, still getting occasional 100% CPU. I think perhaps we should return a different value from ProcessMessages() if we do not want the calling routine to sleep, that allows us to be more explicit than checking that the queues are not empty. It's just difficult to reliably prove that there is no other way out of ProcessMessages() which leaves non-empty queues.",
